1.00	Vitaphone_Racing_Team	Vitaphone Racing	Vitaphone Racing is a German racing team who participate in the FIA GT Championship. The team is actually Bartels Motor &amp; Sport GmbH but runs under the title of their primary sponsor, Vitaphone GmbH. In 2011 Vitaphone Racing was renamed Vita4One. They have successfully raced the Maserati MC12 GT1 since 2005, becoming one of the most successful GT teams in the series with five FIA GT1 Teams' Championship and four FIA GT1 Drivers' Championship. The team consists of 32 people and is led by Rafael Calafell. Their chief drivers are Michael Bartels and Andrea Bertolini.	http://upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/thumb/7/7a/Barthels.jpg/300px-Barthels.jpg
